Steps to setup dynamic nfs 

1. Install nfs in a vm by following the below steps

	a. create a folder for mounting and give user permission

	     sudo mkdir /srv/nfs/kubedata -p 
	     sudo chown nfsnobody:nfsnobody /srv/nfs/kubedata

	b. Install nfs server

	     sudo yum install nfs-utils -y 

     	     systemctl enable nfs-server

	     systemctl start nfs-server

	c. edit /etc/exports file and add the below 
		
		/srv/nfs/kubedata	*(rw,sync,no_root_squash,no_all_squash,insecure)

	d. execute nfs location

		sudo exportfs -rav

	e. Check nfs service in firewall is enabled

	f. Tests nfs server from any kubernetes cluster vm

		install nfs server from step b and run the below command

			mount -t nfs 10.6.1.20:/srv/nfs/kubedata /mnt
			mount | grep kubedata
			umount /mnt
	
2. Install nfs client provisioner

	a. Run RBAC.ymal to create serviceaccounts and clusterrolebinding

	b. Change storageclass name as required and run the class.yaml

	c. Do the below changes in deployment.yaml file
		
	   env:
            - name: PROVISIONER_NAME
              value: mosip/nfs
            - name: NFS_SERVER
              value: 10.4.1.41
            - name: NFS_PATH
              value: /srv/nfs/kubedata
      volumes:
	- name: nfs-client-root
          nfs:
            server: 10.4.1.41

	d. Run deployment.yaml file






